This appears **5 times** total in your log — once during global dependency resolution, and again right at `:bootJar`. This is Gradle 9.4.1 (note: you're on a brand-new Gradle major version) silently **failing to resolve a variant for a dependency and excluding it** rather than erroring out. This is the real lead — something is being silently dropped from resolution, and Gradle 9.x's new variant-aware dependency resolution machinery is involved.

This single fact reframes everything: **your build tooling itself changed** (Gradle 9.4.1, a brand-new major version) between when `v1.6.2` was built and now. That's a far more likely trigger for a classpath/resolution change than re-litigating Jackson version numbers.

